\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid3488920 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 First I'd like to know your name and present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well my name is James - John Lawenson and I - the croft at Airthbank, Fetlar, in the Shetlands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 My date of birth you mean - was 6th of March 1899. Here in Fetlar, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And you've not been married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Not - not married, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Howmany years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - we -d I left - let's see now - well just - well, no, sixteen - sixteen year sixteen year up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And then you were living here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - actually speaking I was at the war from - I - my father and mother shifted down here you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Why did they move down here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well the old house was a small house you see and there was a big family of several - of nine of the family and - the - the landlord agreed to - to help my father - make a - and the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2900983\charrsid14301207 
n you see this house beca}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
me vacant, this place here. The - the residents of the house went to Glasgow, moved to Glasgow and this house was vacant for two or three year and the landlord said to my father, the landlord, the wife, Lady Nicholson as well sa
id, well, the best that you could do is to get that house, that's a big family. So that way - that was the way we came to live here. Well there were several people in but - the - the - came to my father on account of us being - of the big family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 This was a bigger house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes. bigger house, much bigger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And you had nine brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Nine, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When was the eldest born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - oh it was Thomas - Thomas - Thomas that was the - 1895 he was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And the youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 So your mother had nine children in fifteen years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Nine. Seven sons and two daughters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were they fairly evenly spaced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, they were even, indeed, yes, yes. And - it could be added that the big family was the - w
as - very much the rule and the fashion at those days you see. That was a big family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How old was he when I was born? Well to tell the - the father - well - well - he - he would have been about maybe -
 thirty say or there and thereabout.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well he - he - just Fetlar, yes. Father's from Fetlar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What jobs did he have when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - when I was born - when I was born he would have been at the fishing. 
At - at - well that sort of fishing would be about the last they were getting up, that was in the open boats you know. Now it was the six - the six oared boat then. Then that was just about the last time, it was getting - giving up and he - after that he 
w
as at Lerwick as a carrier to the fishing fleet, working for shops, groceries you know. Then after that he - he was a policeman for a while. In the fishing season when there are a lot of people in the Shetlands. Boats you know, and farmers and that. They 
t
ook on extra policemen for the season. You want to know the others? Well after that then he - he worked for - for a United Free Minister, a serving man, that Minister had a sort of a - always been a Minister and a small farmer as well so that there was a 
lot of work to be done, my father got a job there. And that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Otherwise he was a crofter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 A crofter, yes, he used to croft the first with other - with other sidelines these things. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well - well - not - not - not so far as a - a crofter's supposed to be self employed person. But - but there were times though that he was not - not in other employment. At times. You know. Other than the croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well she would been a lot - well she would be - she was younger as my father, a few years younger, say - say about - maybe about twenty - twenty-eight say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh the same, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2900983\charrsid14301207 F}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 etlar again. Just Fedlar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did she have any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - no, she didn't, no. There wasna much chance for women - a place like this you know. Well - there were a few - few dressmakers and fish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2900983\charrsid14301207 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 workers and things, but she didn't really have any. Just - she'd help at the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 She didn't have any jobs after she had the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, none of that, she'd no jobs, no, no. Looking after the - her family you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How many rooms were there in the first house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh now the other - oh the - the - just the two rooms in that. Two rooms. These croft houses was mostly a cottage with two rooms you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did anyone besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no. No, other relations, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your mother have anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well, well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did she pay anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, no. If she was ill or - at times she would be having children that her sister would come down - her sister lived quite near at hand you know. She had - she had three 
other sisters but this one in particular was a very helpful person, that was - that was her sister Mary. My aunt Mary.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2900983\charrsid14301207  She would come down and help q}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 uite a lot. For no pay at all - just for - just for - she liked to help you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh no, no, they all did that at home. All done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, they did quite a lot of that. The Shetlanders were good at that you see, because they had t
o be. They just had to learn that you see. They'd do a lot of sewing and knitting and all that sort of thing. Mending boots and - all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were the clothes you had new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - we always tried to get something new for the best suit of clothing like for church or Sunday school or that, you kept that best.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Where were the clothes bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh now you got that at Lerwick. Lerwick the capital of the island you see, you could get all things there you know. It was bo
ught at Lerwick in - of course boys suits was cheaper those days you know, they were quite cheap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well yes, you had a nice pair of shoes too, boots, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You had to get new ones at Lerwick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, for - Lerwick, oh 
yes, Lerwick - of course it did happen sometimes you see that - that you may got a pair of shoes or - somebody maybe better off as you would say, well I have a pair of boots or shoes, would any of your boys wear that. See, that - that would - that sometim
es happened, but not very - not often that happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Your father didn't make any shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, he didn't make, he could mend - mend shoes you know, he was quite good at that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house like cleaning, cooking, washing up or these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh yes, oh yes, yes, he would yes. For instance now, maybe in cold weather in winter weather like washing potatoes or - or - or - you know, hard dried fish, peeling the skin off it, that sort of t
hing. The - the men of the house generally helped - carried in water for cookery you see - oh yes, they - they helped, oh yes, they helped with the - with the chores about the house, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And things like decorating and repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh 
yes, oh some of the men was quite good at - at - better - at paperhanging and distempering and whenever that was done, oh yes. Did yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What about with the children, did he help dress or undress the children or bath them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - yes - at times, yes, he would - has helped with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did he tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh yes, yes, he told us stories you know, told us stories. We would - we - we would - when we got to school we take home that Blackies Manuals and Grimms Fairy Tales and all - and Andersen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2900983\charrsid14301207 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 s Fairy Tales and that and illustrated books and he would enjoy reading them to us. The stories you know, he would do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did he look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well, yes, he would help to do that. And of course a lot o
f that duties fell to my elder sister when she grew up - grew up to be a young - young - a teenager, she did a lot of looking after you see. She had to when my mother - you know the women on the crofts had to till the soil you know, not - there was no plo
ughs, they'd to till with a sort of a - spade for the purpose - along with my father. They all - the men and the women, the women had to work as hard as the men. And - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well yes, we - yes, well we - well we - we had - we carried water in. See - see there were two kind of wells. There were the well - ordinary water for washing but the well - the - the township had the real good spring water for makin
g tea with a good long way away. We had to - carry that. And then you see, fresh fish was never right except it was boiled in the salt water out of the sea. We had to carry up that water, carry the salt water you know up. So we - we all - and lots of time
s we'd do this. Yes. We'd go to the shop, go messages and - things, oh you'd get all sorts of duties you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How long did you carry on doing these things, did you do them after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 After I left school, yes, right up to the time that I - went in the Royal Naval Reserves for the war, about seventeen - eighteen. But -

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your brothers and sisters have the same tasks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, oh yes, they - they would take their turn. Of course - the older ones did - did the most - all the 
tasks fell to the older members of the family you see, carrying these water and sort of things. But when the other one grew up of course they naturally had to follow to carry as well. And - and cutting peats up was a great thing, that peat work. The ponie
s
 you know was tied together and - things for - for - packs to carry the peats, where the peats was landed the beachers across from the peat hill, landed that the peats had to be flit up, carried with the Shetland pony you know. Well - the youngsters could
n't - couldn't - do that, they could lead the - the ponies, head drops you know. That was something about the Shetland pony at the time would follow children without any trouble at all. So that was a big thing for - for - for the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You say you had to pick them up at the beach, I thought they came from the hills?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Yes, but you see - the - the people that was near to the peat hill took the by land with the ponies, right to the house. But - us in the far side of the island you see, that was far too - 
far too big a task to flit - what we had to do was to put them to a landing place and take them across by boat, we had big boats for the use you see. Across to the beaches, that was nearer, then we had to put them up with the ponies you see. And - and it 
was far nearer and easier for us to take them by sea. That - that's - that's the way far from the peat hill of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did the older children help the younger children with things they found difficult, like dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - oh yes, yes, yes, oh yes, they were - they helped the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did the younger children help the older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well I don't know that the younger ones - maybe didn't help very much you know. They were quite - there was a good deal of co-operation between the two. Of 
course the other - there was always the mischief and that sort of thing with all children and all that sort of thing you know but - on the whole there was none - the families got on very well together you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh yes, oh yes, that was - that - that - I'm afraid that we had - well much more of it in those days than there is today, because we had to go to bed at a certain time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 About what time was it when you were at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well I got about - maybe about ten o'clock at night then you had to go to bed - whether you liked it or not.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When you were small did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well they would when we were very small - yes, they would have seen that we got to bed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 About how old were you when you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh we had to go to bed ourselves - say eight or - eight or thereabout - seven or eight then you go yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How many did you share with, you had to share your bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes, indeed, yes, we did indeed. Maybe three - three of us generally it would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 In one bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How many in the bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well you see, with the children there - there'll be several beds. These kind of beds you see we used a lot, those box}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2900983\charrsid14301207 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
beds. Built into the wall so that it - it really did the - didna cause much obstruction in the house. There was a door that closed and opened in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 If there were only two rooms in the house you must have been quite crowded?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh yes, yes, and the big family that we had, but I'll tell you in that case - if - if it was made - they tried to fix up - make a ladder so that you could go up - on the - just right up at the top of the ceiling like a - in the room - 
they tried to make do - a bed up there. Fix it up as best as you could you see. That was tried a lot and quite successful. The only thing you found up there was the smoke. From the chimneys. That was murder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You mean there weren't proper chimneys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, the smoke seemed somehow to get - across - to the upstairs, across the other room someway or another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How many of you slept upstairs then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh maybe two or three sometimes. And up the stairs - it was really up a sort of a ladder and a hole - a square hole was in the roof.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And the others were in the other two rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were your parents in one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well yes, and they had the next in the other, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you ever have baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well bath - bath - only bat
h - no, I'm afraid not. You see - for - for water itself and the sea and the lock were far too cold and - and we didn't have facilities in the houses for - for baths so what we really did we washed parts, first one half and then the other you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When did you wash?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh we had - there were tubs - oh there were plenty of places to wash, there were tubs and basins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Inside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Sometimes inside the house. We'd a bit of privacy. The boys would - well the girls would go into their end 
while the wash was going in. They just managed to make do as best they could you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How often did you get clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - you - you - every Saturday, generally. And - and - and you just had to take care of the clothes you had b
ecause - it's not like now you bee because you just - the clothes was rather scarce among the big families.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What was the difference between the two rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well - well - the - the living room or the kitchen place if you like where they sat
 or - where you dined or had your feed, it was called the but end. The other one was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864161\charrsid14301207 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
en end. So you - you know the word - we but and bed if you remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864161\charrsid14301207 H}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 arry Lauder's songs, there's a week dock and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864161\charrsid14301207 D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 oris, we'll drink in a wee but and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864161\charrsid14301207 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 en. That means to say the but and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864161\charrsid14301207 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
en, that was what - that was Scots, that's Shetland as well. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864161\charrsid14301207 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
en end was - was where your parents slept and that was a better end like. So if a man is to come along to see you it was the fashion to take them in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864161\charrsid14301207 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 en end, you had a bit of - a sort of a table or - sort of - took them in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864161\charrsid14301207 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
en end usually, the better end.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Which end did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh now, the but end, the kitchen, sitting in, was the fireplace in. That was the eating place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 That was where your mother cooked as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, yes, yes, that's where she cooked the meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did she have to cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - in those days you see it was just the open fire. Well latterly - no, no, the stoves had come in but - when I was a boy they hadn't g
ot the stove. It was just the open fire. They would have a - an oven. For baking. They'd - then there was - father put a live coals - things on the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 The oven was a separate thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 That you put over the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 That's on the baking
 day they would put the - hot cinders and things on the top of the iron lid to make it even burning you see in the oven, that was the usual way. And then they had a - iron - thing - with ribs you know, ribbed, they would put that at the fire with the coal
s
 to bake hotcakes on. And then they had a frying pan and they would make pancakes and that sort of things on. So they - they had all the cooking things and then - then - all the pots and pans you know, kettles for boiling water, all that sort of thing. Th
at was an open fire. Latterly of course they got that stoves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When did the stoves come in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - when the stoves came in - really during the first world war quite a lot got them. The merchant in the place ordered - ordered them. You know. V
ictor and Chandlers stoves was the names of them. They were quite good stoves you know. But of course I suppose it would be very - oh I think there's some on the Shetlands yet. Some of the people have them, we all have this kind of thing now. This cooker.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - I - I think that breakfast generally about nine o'clock. They had - they - they mostly had what they called the morning cup. Oh that was earlier, maybe eight o'clock. A cup of tea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When was the main breakfast then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh nine or half past nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were all members of the family present for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, yes - they were all present, yes, yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did you usually have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - the most of the people you s
ee, they had - they kept some - sell a few if they could at that but they always had some hens. You know. And - they could always manage egg. And then the pigs was, kept a lot, every family, one or two pigs. And - that - that - lasted a good long time, a 
good pig you know, and it took care - and they didn't - and - with the flesh, they tried to spin it out you know and that lasted a good while so they had a rasher of bacon with their egg. Something. And - and porridge. That was a fair thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well dinner - dinner was just about ready between half past one and two o'clock. We'd potatoes figured largely there. Course you had soup, what they called potato soup, or tatie soup. That was a - the big pot came in there. 
And then you had cabbage, boiled and fish of course. All got some salted fish in the wintertime and summer you see we'd fresh fish. So there was - there was - there was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When did you have the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well that - that - the evening mea
l was about maybe - oh five o'clock. But that was just a plain affair, bread and - and - tea, anything that - summertime you would have - at the churning time - milk you would have - buttermilk was, you would have Shetland cheese, that was curd milk, did 
I
 tell you about that before sometime? Oh well - well - well that as you know they used a big long barrel like churns, narrow things they churned in. Churned for butter you know. Well that - when the butter was taken off there was the left - buttermilk - t
h
e white buttermilk. Well then that - some of that was kept for baking. Well there was sour - pail at the side of the door you know. But - they had to put it to some use, a large lot like that, so what they did do with at - about maybe a two and a half gal
l
on of boiling water, they boiled it on the fire, so then they add to that. Well the result was that the curds were settled down you see, pour in the curd. And that - was run, off the water you see, that was kept for drinking. That took the name of bland t
hen. That's drinking stuff. Well it was sour, some even called it Shetland beer. 'Cos sour - it was - proper drink you know for hot weather. Well that white stuff was taken off you see. They put a fine linen so it - so it - open linen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid950096\charrsid14301207 , gause stuff so the water ran }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 out. Then it was hung up to drip so it would get w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid950096\charrsid14301207 hi
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 te like cheese. White stuff. That was quite filling. A lot - you know, you couldn't eat all that but it was so filling you know that that went a long way. That was a great thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did you have to drink, anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well - well - you mean - do you mean in the way of - of-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 With meals normally in the daytime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well you take tea but some of the - a lot of young people drink milk. That was a great thing. If you had go
od cows you know, good dairy cows. Good milking cows there was always a good supply of milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you have a different more special diet on Sundays or any other particular occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well, yes, Sun - there always - Sunday - you always kept so}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7149234\charrsid14301207 
mething better than usual for S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 unday. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What kind of things would you have on Sunday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well when you were shopping - when they were shopping, there were - there were - get some fancies or some things - perhaps special - a few cake
s or fancy biscuits and say, now we'll keep that for the Sunday. You know, at the weekend you know, at Shetland was called - the weekend was called the helle - helle. That's the end of the week. That's a Norse word. Helle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You said your mother baked her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did she make any other things herself at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Any jam or pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, yes, yes. Well - well - oh yes, they - they - there was rhubarb jam making - wasn't so much - oh they would make - t
hey would make - I'll tell you what they would make a lot of. A use of the fish, fish liver, fish row. They'd make all sorts of diets with that you know. And - stuff the fish head, the - the liver and - they would put - process the liver, break it up so -
 pick out any things - impurities, you know, they didn't think proper to - to - impurities like and then break it up with - with meal or - or ground}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7149234\charrsid14301207 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 meal. And then put pepper and salt and that sort of thing and - into the head. Well that was called crappin.
 That was very delicious. And then when - other - and then they put the liver in the head and - and mixed it with fish and broke that up with the - the livers and put salt and pepper, the taste of - that was called stapp. Then of course - I told you about
 
the various - maybe in the form of - you maybe have that before. Oh I see, I see, well they made a lot - you know the fish they called the cole fish, you maybe don't know - well it's similar to pilchard. We call it the pilchard but it's really not the pil
c
hard. It's the cole fish. They're the small size. Well when it's a small size, maybe about - say - four and a half or five inches that - that size well then - when it's fat quite a good liver on that fish. It's delicious fish. It's fried or boiled or eate
n
 various ways, but then if you want a delicacy - then you would - you would push out the guts of - clean 'em out then put back the liver, you've got two livers then, then you fry this on the pan, you know these are called mou gelders. Mou gelders. Well th
e
n, if you - if you want to keep the livers of then - and gather the livers, put them on a frying pan and burn them. But you should leave the liver as these cook you know, leave it to get smaller. You mix that up with meal. Put that meal, you know the good
 
meal that they bake because there's a lot of fat there. All the - you needn't prepare that if you have a weak stomach. That's called crampies. You needn't try that, it'll repeat badly on you you need a good stomach for that. Yes, yes. And of course variou
s - really too numerous to mention was the use of fish. Then they'd break up the roe and - and mix that with meal. The roe of the fish you know.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7149234\charrsid14301207  And - that was called - swa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 atts. And so on and so on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - no,
 but they are brewing some now. What they call home brewed but they are brewing - in various parts of Shetland. We didn't brew in Fetlar though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your parents grow their own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, yes, but of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did they grow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well the veg - all the veg that they used - the crofters at any rate - was just potatoes, turnips and - and cabbage, put in a few onions and a few carrots. But they didn't have all the fineries that you would have in England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 There wasn't any fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, no, no fruit unless you bought it. There were no - no - only they - they could some of them that had shelter they could - could grow the strawberries you know. Oh yes, yes, indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, they didn't, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did they buy any fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well at the Christmas - at the Christmas time they would have bought a few apples and oranges you know. That was just about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did they buy any tinned fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, you could - tinned fruit, oh yes, you could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your parents buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well not much, not - not much of that. That was considered a luxury, that was only conserved for the - for the rich people. These tinned things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What livestock did you keep on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well -
 well - you see in those days - the crofts were small but now with the declining population as crofts get - vacant they're to other people, the other men. Well in those days - in those days if you had a one croft, that was - that was about - six or seven 
acres arable land, hill pasture as well, there we kept two cows. And then two or three younger ones, and some sheep and some ponies. Maybe half a dozen of ponies at - that was mainly for peat work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, hens. They had maybe - up to about a score of hens. And some of them had ducks of course. And some had geese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You didn't though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh no, no, no, we - we didn't keep geese, no, no. Or ducks. But lots had them, lots of crofters had them though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Who looked after all these animals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh well - well you see, really speaking lots of these - birds, well I'm not meaning the hens, they had to be fed regularly, but ducks and geese, they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7149234\charrsid14301207 scavengers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 , they find - found food for themselves you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But in your family who looked after your animals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh well - the - the older ones. Children and my father and - well be the older ones - my older brothers as they got up, they looked after the lot of that. And sisters. Well - they were just - anyone, the members of the family.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And you had either fish or meat of some kind every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Every day. Well we - we wouldn't have fresh meat though. No, no, not fresh meat. That was - that was an occasional thing, you had the fresh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you have bacon?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh
 yes. Salt bacon, oh yes, oh there was salt, yes, salt - salt fish. When you butchered the animals then you had the fresh stuff. But after that of course you had to put it to salt you see.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you get rabbits from time to time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, the rabbit, oh yes, the rabbit was hunted a lot those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You didn't do any poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, no, it - it wasn't considered poaching. People only too glad for you to take the rabbit away if you could get a hold of him. They only thing that you h-d to
 watch you see - if the landlord liked his shepherd to see that you didn't tear out the stones of the dyke so to make the dykes fall, that was - he watched you though, he watched you with the glass - binoculars - to see that you didn't tear out the - we -
 we hunted the rabbits but - he - he - he didn't want us - us to tear - tear down the stones - for damaging the walls of the - the dykes and that, stone dykes you see. Oh we hundred the rabbit all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having less food so that the rest of the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, big families, that - that was very often - a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you remember that in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes I mind there was - lots of times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your father have more than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, no, he - they wouldn't - they wouldn't have - have eaten more than - left the children hungrier. If - if - if there were that much in the house - if there was not much in the house - they - share alike with the rations what's going sometimes. 
But your not taking down the old house, I could tell you lots about that but are you not interested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well if - if you - if - if you had to talk or if you had to - well you could ask - yes, you could talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were you expected to keep quiet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh no, no, they would - they would - they wouldn't expect you to keep quiet if you had to say anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Could you choose what you wanted to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, you - well no, you had to take what was there. Y
ou couldn't choose, if it was bread - home baked bread you were glad of a piece of the home baked bread - with home butter on it, you were very glad - you couldn't choose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well they - they would - they would ask what - what was - is anything wrong with you. Whether you stomach ached or whether you were sick or - what was wrong, if you were in pain. They'd ask you, what's wrong with you? You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You couldn't just be fussy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, none of that, you couldn't be fussy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, would you ask someone to pass it or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - you - you - if it was on the opposi
te side of the table you would have said, would you pass us the salt? And just - we should do that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, oh yes, you could ask for a second helping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, no, no, no, that - that in a croft house was no - no, when we got older you know - and we knew we had to go out to the world that - maybe go down to a lodging house in Lerwick, then we - we start
ed to acquire how we should sit and hold our fork and knife. But not as children. Not as children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - you could have done it but it was - it was not generally done. You - if you were eating there 
for your meal you didn't bother about - only I suppose if you wanted you could have done but - we're too much intent on - on getting -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 There was too many of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, too many, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - we
ll you could leave the table - well I suppose if you had to leave the table you just said - we - were well enough mannered to say, excuse me - if you had to go out. But you didn't generally leave the table until you were all had your meal you see. Drop of
f one after the other, that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did all your family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh yes, yes, they all sat at the table, oh yes. There were maybe some outside at some - they would have to go without if they hadn't got back from the shop or - but - but normally they would have all sat at the table, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you have the same places, did you always sit in the same place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - the older ones, my father and mother - older members of the family would have had their - but the younger one
s, they just moved about, it didn't matter so much with them. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How was the meal served, who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - it would have been - well generally my mother - soup - she would bale it up with a ladle you know or - sometimes my father wou
ld do it. Would cut if it was - pork or meat, he - he would give a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7149234\charrsid14301207 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
and with the carving, but it was generally them. Maybe my older sister would - would - she's - a servant in Edinburgh now, she would - would - the other girls, she would do some of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh no, well - just around the table as you sat. Well - oh they would give to the seniors first. They would get the first serving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Where did the young ones sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Where did 
they sit? Well - the young ones sometimes would - would sit on a small stool, when they were young - too young to get to table had a small round stool which would give them some - some feeding on a plate, the young.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Who would feed them before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - oh me mother - generally me mother - me mother would always feed them. Always feed them. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well yes, yes, well - our mother was - it be true to say, was a - a ver
y intelligent woman, naturally she was a good singer you know and she could - made a better - she could have gone - lots of people thought that she married young and had a big family she could have done something with her voi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12680468\charrsid14301207 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 e you know, she was a good scholar at the school, so she was all right, mother to talk to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Sometimes people think that Victorian families were all rather grim.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 I know, I know. Yes. But of course she was a strict mother bringing us up you know. Very much so, like that sort of thing you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, indeed - yes, yes. Oh yes, indeed she did. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 If you had any worries could you go and tell her about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, we could do that, oh yes, there were no - there was
 no - there were no differences there, yes you could, yes. Well I took - if we had worries we'd go to me father first. I think so. I believe that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Would the boys go to the father and the girls to the mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, I - I still think that I would go
 to my father first though. I have that - feeling. He was an exceptional fine man, my father. And - and I think we'd have been inclined to - I would anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 He was easier to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, yes, he was easier, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well I know - oh but I can - I think that's easily answered. The standard of behaviour with children with older people in fact their parents growing up was - was really high as you will learn a lot at the school, we had a
 Highland teacher, Miss McLeod and there were so much went there at the week was set apart for teaching manners. You see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What kind of things were you taught?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - lots of things. How - how to behave, how to speak to your elders and - and you always say please and thank you and you got the -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How were you supposed to speak to your elders, what kind of things should you observe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well - well - you wasn't supposed to be cheeky. You know. You were suppose to be submissive like - not
 - not too forward you know. Had to treat them as your superiors. Not - just any old way. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well - not - so much that all the - if they s
een you bullying your brothers and sisters - any time you like, you know - any - well if they see you not playing the game, then they'll - bought you up probably, gave you a rap across the knuckles. If they thought you were just doing a bullying business 
or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Of that - outside the family? Oh well they didn't expect you to be a softie. But they wouldn't - they wouldn't have liked you to have got into any tro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12680468\charrsid14301207 uble you see, in the neighbour}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 hood, they wouldn't like to seen you coming in with a black eye for instance, been fighting. They thought it better to keep out of that. to settle your quarrels without -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But if some other child hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, oh yes, 
they would - they would question you - what are you fighting for. Who began the fight or what did it start over. So they'd want to know about it you see, kind of thing. How - how it came about and that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well I - I think it - the chief aim was - they would like you to have gotten on in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did they think that meant, what kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well - well - well - the getting on to make sor
t of a - so that you - to make money - to live on, you see what I mean. And get on in life so you could - you could - well if you got settled down in life that you could - that you could fight your won battles like and you - that was the sort of idea.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 If you were going to get on in life what kind of opportunities were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh - oh well, I'll tell you, the master ship at - boys - boys when they got - had to go to sea. They - they hoped that you'd get on there and maybe - you'd get on, progress 
and make money and so on, maybe if you want to get on for your tickets and all that sort of thing, you know, that was in their mind - to get on in life. Yes. Does that answer your question?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your parents bring you to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - yes and no, they - they werena too fussy about - you see, I - I don't know if I can explain that to you. You }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12680468\charrsid14301207 see. To a - to a - perhaps a le}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 sser degree than some parts - these island life and people are primitive. Maybe not so much
 as some people but they are that sort of - of something, as compared with you Southern people. Well - well - well being a rather primitive race they - they didn't expect all that much of you. See? For instance. The - the Western Isles men in the far lyin
g islands of the Hebrides, he's quite happy if he -if he gets a lots of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12680468\charrsid14301207  birds to eat and feathers to s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
ell, see? There's a little cottage - they used a little black house but the betters that now. Well there's not a great deal expected of that you know. The 
Shetlander to a lesser degree were something the same. He was a primitive race. See what I mean? When Doctor Hibberd came to these islands first - well he - he - he observed a certain amount of primitiveness about the whole thing. He went - when they were
 cutting the peats you know. You know what cutting peats are, where they have to take off a - a piece of ea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12680468\charrsid14301207 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
th first before they got down to the peats. And they were just fumbling around any old how, they wouldn't lay it down to grow flat the grass again. H
e would say, well why are you doing that? Oh it doesn't matter. A certain primitiveness about the whole thing. It's strange the way the - it doesn't matter. Would you not lay it flat? Oh no, it doesn't matter. It's a primitiveness about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh no, no, those days, no, no, here again there was certainly a - a very strict upbringing. They wouldn't tolerate swearing at all. They wouldn't use - say - there was no - no - they wouldn't like that in the house at
 all. Any misbehaviour, swearing at all. Didn't - that wasn't tolerated. Well they didn't - I'll tell you what they didn't like. They didn't like to be bad mannered towards elderly people. If you - if you - if you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What kind of things were bad manners then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well I'll tell you, I - I remember woman as I remember used to come that way being at the shop and she carried the stuff on a pony, you see. And - and we'd always speak to - we - we - we make - do something so she'd spe
ak, and she had what you would call a stoppage in her speech. And we would do something to make her speak, and when she got excited -b-b-b-b-b-b - like that and we wo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12680468\charrsid14301207 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 ld laugh at that and thought that splendid sport but our parents had seen us doing that t
hey'd tell us off. You see, that was bad manners, you know what I mean. Any bad - any bad manners towards your elders was considered very bad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - not all that much. No, they - if you 
were asked, you wouldn't be - they may ask you a thing and if father said, boy - what do you think of so and so, but - if they asked you - you wasn't supposed to talk all that much when grown ups were speaking. It was pretty - that was observed very much.
 So.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 If you did something hour parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - if you did something your parents disapproved of? Do you mean in a small - in a larger sense like - do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How did the parents control the children and wha
t happened if the children did things they shouldn't do, this could be big things or little things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well - oh no, they were - they were - keeping reminding you of the fact that you had transgressed. They would keep reminding you that you had gone from the straight a bit and you have to mend your ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 This old woman who had an impediment in her speech?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 If they found about that what would they do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh they - they - they would - they would - they wouldn't have like it, my mother even might have given you a good }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13964701\charrsid14301207 sm}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 ack across your bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh - just with her hand or - or something. Or a piece of - of leather - belt. They didn't like that sort of thing you see. They thought it a reflection on their upbringing of the children, if that happened. You see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You mentioned your mother giving you a whack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your father ever?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well, it had to be pretty bad before he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What kind of things would be have to step in on then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh - well - it had to be pretty bad before - before he - before he - before he did anything. Had to be pretty bad, you had to - maybe if I was - was - was hurting him, when I was a youngster then my father would give me a knock wouldn't he
. Maybe that sort of thing. Yes, you see, that sort of way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Both your parents would discipline you but for ordinary things it would be your mother more than your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, yes, much more, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - once I'm afraid - lots - lots of times. Sometimes - I might -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Is there one time that stands in your mind perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - I'll see if I can mind now. Oh yes, well if I - I - if I - I was - I suppose I w
as - if I was - I remember was breaking some crockery, some crystal things that she - my mother got at her wedding present, a fine - kind of a sugar basin and my brother George and I broke that skylarking, we got a good hot bottom, both of us, for that. Y
es.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How Did you feel about being punished then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - oh that - well we - we expected it, so we got it. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You got a hot bottom, you didn't feel too bad otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, no, we expected that. We knew it was very provoking. Yes, yes. We expected it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well I - it - it would be from both I expect. From both of them. And - and -
 add - adding - add to that the - the - the up - the teaching we had at school was a big part of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When you had a birthday would it be any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, there were no birthdays observed. Used to say, well that was his b
irthday, he's so and so today. But there were no presents or anything. No, not - not - no, no, that was - I never had a - they just remarked that that's your birthday. Somebody said, boy that's your birthday, did you know. And I'd say, yes, well - I say.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh well, you mean, how did they keep - is that how did they keep? Oh well, Christmas was a big day you know. Christmas was a great day in Shetland. It was ke
pt - what they call the Erger was on the fifth of January for a while. That was changed over with the Ministers said well you - you're wrong, you're at the far end of the line, keep Christmas the same day as we are, on the twenty-fifth, the same. So we sa
i
d, all right. But Christmas was a great - you know, perhaps you - you - you'll know that Christmas observance among the Scandinavian folk - that was a very great thing, it was mostly the religious - the religious people you know, the better of their Savio
ur was - was a great thing looked on you know, so they would make preparations days before, you know, to keep Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What actually happened on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well they - they would start to make the preparations - they - they would hav
e this pig and they would try to have it butchered to fit in with Christmas. They'd boil a piece of pork - and cabbage to season the thing. A big piece. And - then - with the bladder of the pig, they cured the salt that did and make a football. They would
 
make it for the youth of the place. Then all the youth of the place gathered to play football. And then they'd have lamplight, sometimes with the little candles, the various candles, put in the window you know. Well the breakfast was made very early and t
h
ey'd generally have it - but younger people wouldn't get that, they would generally have a drop of - of spirit sometime, the older people. But you - but the younger children wouldn't get that. Sometimes the old men would gather and play the football on - 
o
n the larger scale. And - we all - the young fellows would gather and then they would - after a time they would go for - oh their breakfast was had, that - that was a big - all the people, mother's, they would bake homemade cakes and - they could get the 
s
tuff from the shops like, currants and raisins and all that sort of thing. And - oatcakes and all sorts of things and they'd have a good feed. You - you were supposed to have a good tuck-in a feed, at Christmas Day. And then I'll tell you another thing. I
t
 was good luck to have something - new to wear at Christmas. And if you didna have something to wear - they called to - you were sort of - they laughed at you and if you didna have something to wear you know what they called you then. A Yule Erger. A Yule
 Erger if you did not buy the new to put on at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did that mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well - well Christmas is the Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13964701\charrsid14301207 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 le season you know. Well Erger is - is just something - him that didn't have. You - you know that. Yule Erger. Anybody that didna
 have anything new to put on. And you just spent the day - of course if you were too young to go to the village dance at night you should have to stop home. But it was generally bad weather and snow and your parents wouldna - wouldna allow the younger one
s to go to t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13964701\charrsid14301207 he dance. But you had - just a g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 ood day you may say at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you have presents at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - not at those days. Not - not very much. No, there wasn't much by way of presents. It was more eating and drinking. Or playing
 football - and dancing. But the presents I'm afraid didn't come 'til later you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - yes, I'll tell you what was a great - because it could be bought cheaply - you had to - well a son of t
he house mostly had a violin you know, but for the youngsters you would save up to get a Jews Harp, you know what that is, and - and - and that - and that - what do you call it - and - and a - mouth organ. You know, a Jews Harp is the one you play like th
at.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And you had one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, we all had one, we saved up and they could get for three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13964701\charrsid14301207  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 pence maybe or tuppence and they were cheap you know. That was a great thing. And then - a small mouth organ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, they could nearly all sing - they could nearly all sing. Most of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you ever make music together as a family then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - yes, yes, there would be, yes, yes, they - they would sing - songs, yes, they would sing. Maybe - your mot
her would tell you to sing a Christmas carol or something you know. They would tell you. Yes, yes. We used to sing - my - older brother was fine singer. My mother would make us sing, Once In Royal David's City, was a lonely cattle shed. You know? Oh yes, 
yes, indeed we'd sing at Christmas. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 At other times of the year as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - yes, occasionally, yes, yes, we would - yes, sing songs we were learning at the school. We'd maybe sing them together you know. The ones we'd be taught at the 
school. I think there was far more singing then than what's now. No, there's not much, no, no, there was far more. Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well me father was - had a sense of humour, he - he would play - what 
would he play? Oh now he means - that was later, that - when we were younger. Well I'll tell you what he'll sometimes do, he'll set off paper boats. They were made of paper and a calm day, you know, we were flitting the p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13964701\charrsid14301207 ea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 ts up then he'll take down some s
o - that was to keep us in good trim you know, so we flitted the peats you know. He would set off the boats this fine - fine calm day you know, saw our boat made with paper you now. And oh all sorts of things. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh - well - I'm afraid that there were not - well there would have been a few - mostly. Of course you see in those days you know as - perhaps you'll be aware of that - a lot of the children so they got was - was - was religious teaching. Lik
e the shorter Chatechism you know, you get that a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 So you'd have some religious books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Yes. Some - and maybe - well the Pilgrim's Progress was a great book you'd find in the house you see. And - of course there's one thing about it you see, 
when you got a bit older you could always take home books from the school library. And that helped a lot you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you have newspapers or magazines at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well, yes, my mother always got the - the Friends - or merchants, would give that one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13964701\charrsid14301207 they called the Christian Herald}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
 that you've seen that book there. Well its a religious book. So - a lot of the books consisted of the religious readings you know in that day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, they could read, oh - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Would you see them sitting down reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh - my father would read to us and enjoyed it. We would take home that big I that library - and that - that Grimms fairytales and things, a big - coloured pictures and he - he will enjo
y that reading - Aladdin and the Wonderful Lamp and Beauty and the Beat and - and - and all that you know, the - the - all that sort of - he'd read out aloud, we'd gather around him you know. Yes. All that kind and Sleeping Beauty and all that. And he ono
y
ed that too. He enjoyed that was well you know, Jack the Giant Killer and Jack and the Beanstalk, all that, he - he liked that. The next night he'd get to read the other - maybe - he would be reading us a - well - maybe Jack the Giant Killer the first nig
ht, he'd get to read the Cinderella and the Glass Slipper the next night and - and we felt that he enjoyed that as well as we did you know. Yes, I know. We could mind that, yes, yes
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - I - I can remem
ber funerals, I know, and - in the district. Maybe not so much in the family but I can remember them - in the neighbour - oh yes, I can remember my grandmother's funeral you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Who attended it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - well - in those days you see - in those day
s there were - it'll take me a bit of time to explain it if you have a lot - well - well the olden times in Shetland a funeral, there was so many people on the Island that sufficient to go to the graveyard with the remains was called the Leek. That meant 
t
o say as the Aith and Funsie was. Houlie and Tresta another district was Leek. Northdale and that district so that - see - unless a very notable person like a laird or a minister or a landlord the whole lot of the island would be present. But normal times
 
the Leek would do. Except where relations was now. Relations - maybe if you had relations in the West side of Feltar they'd be invited. They just called that people outside the Leek. If they belonged to the funeral they might say - who was at the funeral?
 Well - the - the Leek and six or seven outside the Leek, you understand what I mean by - that was relations maybe. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How close relations would come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh cousins and - cousins and that sort of thing. Second and third cousins and first cousins.
 Yes, yes, that - that - that was outside - relations. You see. They lowered down the remains in the churchyard, all the relations, you see. Did you want to know how a funeral was conducted? Is that what you were asking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Your grandmother's funer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13964701\charrsid14301207 al}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 , the Leek would have come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Plus some relations from outside?
