\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What clothes did people wear for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - well they always - they had - they put on their best Sunday clothes and - you mean the far off - oh they p
ut Sunday clothing and they had - generally a bowler hat that they put - but they always wore a black tie. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 This was when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes. Yes, and every people had what they called the funeral tie, a black tie kept for the use of funerals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 That was for mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Yes, yes, and always the black tie, that showed that they were - respect, I mean, that's what they wore to show that they were - at the funeral, always a black tie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You were going to say something generally about funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well I was wondering - if you wanted - details of a - of a funeral. Well - when the person died - when - when the person died of course - the relations was there and the body was there of course and laid out and then of course an
y carpenter - wooden men on the island would make the coffin. But in earlier times the coffin was just a plain white wood. But after about maybe say - thirty year ago then of course the undertakers took in the black mounting you see, that you can buy now,
 
you know, first of all it was built. And - another thing is doe away with now, it's what they called the kisting. Well - when the body was put into the - in - in the coffin you know they'd - all the female friends around the district would be - neighbours
,
 relations, anybody knew the deceased person, it was always women generally, was invited to a sort of a - not a wake what they have in Ireland but more of a sad occasion they would gather and they would have tea. And it was a sort of to condole with the m
o
urners you know, they would just gather around and - a sort of a solemn gathering and - the body would be - in the coffin then. And they would just gather around and say, well yes, he was a very fine neighbour, and we'll miss her greatly and - offer their
 
sorrow for her - sort of a - and have tea and then - bid goodbye to the mourners and cheer them up and say God would be standing by in this time of trouble. That was called the kisting. The kisting Well - well - well - well the kisting - the kisting was a
 chest. The coffin was a sort of a chest you know. That was putting the body into the coffin call the kisting. That was putting it into the chest. The kisting. If y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13964701\charrsid14301207 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 u understand that. And then of course at the - at the funerals though, that's another thing,
 by the way, I'll say fortunately, was - was they had to have - not a - later became the - they would get refreshments, but they had to carry these coffin - the body a long way to the churchyard they would have a set tea. They would have tea passed round 
t
hem and bread. Might have been that they had to carry the remains and - and things for the use you see. Well of course all that was all done by car and that you know. Had to be carried by hand and things. Eight - eight or nine mean that they were relieved
,
 well they thought that to do that they were allowed part of the way they had to start off having a cup of tea. That was done away with. After that it became a glass of whisky. See, latter years. And then that was dropped altogether. Now the funerals is a
ll church you see. So that's how that was done. Regarding the particulars of a funeral.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were you taken our visiting neighbours and friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were you taken out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was there a fairly formal system of going visiting other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - when you got - a bit older. See - what - what - what - I'll tell you what, when - boys got youths they would do a lot of road patrol - walking over the roads on a fine moonlight night. Maybe if - if there were girls having a cooking class at the
 school or that with the teacher, would have cooking classes you know, and church guilds. The boys was pretty - it wasn't long for them to start to take walking the roads after these girls and so on and so on. But you were - there no one take you - you st
art to go out yourself you see. There were no - rather what's behind you there, no T.V's or - or radios. Well you may have the gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13964701\charrsid14301207 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 phone or that sort of thing but you did a lot of your entertainment at other houses playing cards and draughts was a great th
ing. And you went a lot out the houses, you visited this house, this night then go to another house. And do you know what that was called? Well that also had a Norse word and you would never - a difficulty to pronounce - do you know what they called that 
t
hen? Going from house to house. And that some night you'll go away to there, maybe have a game of cards, whist or bridge or playing that you know. Then the next time you say, well we'll go to - Houbie district next day. Then maybe we'll go up to Airth or 
that. Well that was called going Hous a mella. Hous a mella. Say that now. That's right. That - that was just going from house to house. For entertainments sake you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 This would be the young people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Young people. And - and youths and that sort of thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you go visiting with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, no, not with your parents, no, no, no. Not with your parents. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were you ever taken shopping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, we'll be taken shopping and - oh yes, yes, you had to go - indeed you had to do your shop - then after a bit o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13964701\charrsid14301207 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 der you have to do the shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But you wouldn't go to Lerwick or somewhere like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, not to Lerwick, no, no, no. See those shops on the island would supply your wants you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you go out just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 To where would you say? Oh to the fishing you mean? Well - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You would go out fishing with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes. Well - well - would we go out with our father much? Where would - oh yes, yes, yes, aye, yes, we 
would go. Well - can you mind where we went a time with him? Oh we - we might have a walk with him, he might take us to - if we were going to look for some of the ponies or anything. You see, well just go - we're going for a walk to have a look for the po
nies, if we see such a - sheep or mares or ponies or cattle or anything up to the hill he'd take you. Just for company's sake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you remember any outings with your parents like Bank Holidays or anything like that, would you ever go off the island with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh no, no, no, no, not al all, no, no. We wouldn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - since - you mean when I was a boy? No, not as young, no, we - no, no. No, no. The truth of the matter would be you see there that very
 few of the big families had the money to go for holidays. You would have to pay your way and there have to pay your digs. We didn't have the money. That's the - that's the - fact of the matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - Saturday - would be the day you wouldn't be at school. Saturday was something of a holiday. And - you would just - what they would call - knock around, doing one little odd job or another. You would maybe fetch - you would maybe fetch salt wa
ter you now what I mean by that? Well you see fish - fresh fish was never thought - properly cooked - boiled unless it was boiled with water out of the sea. You had to go down with a bucket - and carry up a bucket of salt water. To boil the fish in. And b
o
th parents would know if it was from the beach part and they would know that. Do you know why? Well they knew - there's a fresh water burn coming down the beach and they would know that it wasn't just quite so salt as it would - the other place would have
 
been from. The hole - they called it the salt water hole. My mother would know if - if - if we had taken from the beaches because the water - the burn running down would make it fresher. Would - wouldn't just he the proper thing. And then we'd have to go 
to the well. The well. That's a well a good bit from the district, special good well and made splendid tea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 So you had special water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 That was extra good water, you would have to carry a keg you know what the keg is do you? A barrel full of wate
r, maybe go two or three times. So you did't have to go out Sunday. See what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did you do on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, well in my day Sunday was the day that was strictly kept. If - if - if - if you were young well you had to go to Sunday scho
ol. And - if you were passed that age you had to go with your parents to the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How old did you change?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - at - at about maybe - how old did we give up Sunday school - was it thirteen. Fourteen - fourteen. But you had to go to the church 
in any case. And - sit with your parents - lasted long sermons. Mind you, our own Minister could preach very very long wise sermon, but it didn't matter, we had to be there and listen. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you wear special clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, you put on your Sunday best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well you - you would have a - a bit of a suit that you kept for Sunday. It was better just - kept - jacket and trousers not bad condition you know and a shirt, and a - and a - and a collar thing. And a tie. And the collar was called a dickie, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you wear a hat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, no hat, just a cap or your bare head, didn't wear hats. No hats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you play any games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, no, you weren't - you couldn't play games, you were sup
posed to keep that, it was a case of remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy you see, no games. If - if - if you did to keep out of the way of your - of your parents. Yes. You did, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And you weren't supposed to work on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Not work, no, - no, no working. Of course, you - you would do the works that's a ne}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16592850\charrsid14301207 cess}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
ity. Supposing say a - a - supposing say you - you had to milk your cow, you had to go - well you put your cattle out on the grass and that. But that - that work was necessity, or a
ny sick animal you could go to the shop for some castor oil for a sick calf you know, anything like that. But you weren't - you couldn't - you werena allowed the other - wicked - weekend - weekday - therapies or games you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How often did your parents go to church on Sundays?
