\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, oh yes, Mr Carson - when he came, he - he had picnics a
nd things, oh yes, yes, yes. There were yes, and then there were soirees, you know what that is do you? Religious - they were a soiree, well tha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13246275\charrsid14301207 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 's a concert thing. To do - a religious concert - hymns and - and you all had to take part at that 'til - thus was recitations and singing and the children of the Sunday school you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How often did that happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Once a year. Then you - you had your tea and you got a prize if you - for attendance. And - you got an orange and apple and a bag with - with 
- with - buns and things in. But - they would prick the bag, you know what I mean, you know what I mean. You could see all these prick marks in the bag you know, all like that. You mind that? Yes, yes, yes.
