\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 ldn't let you - oh you had to go. Yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did the church run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - no. They - they didn't. They didn't you see because you see there was really not much need for that because - there were no drinking bars or things here. Of course you could - if anybody wanted - New Year or Christmas if they wanted drink th
ey just could get it from Lerwick or here or there, just send for it. But the church didn't run any temperance clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You did have prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But you didn't have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no family prayers, no. Not at night time, but they did - the children age before did - they had family prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your father take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - not all that much. At those days you see, they had just that little - Liberal in Mr Western, they kept him in and they 
knew he was a Liberal and he was in all that time and that's all they knew about it, there was nobody proposed in those days and they didn't bother much about politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Your father just supported this Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, they all voted for Western. And the post for many many years and that was that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Why do you think he was Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well you see the truth of the matter was that - that - that - it was - there were no Labour in those days, I don't know - it was just Liberal and Conservative an
d - and nobody opposed this Western - Captain Western was his name. And he just get - was - there was one that - if they did there were one but he - he - they al got - I'll tell you why you see, it got into the heads of these crofters act see and - and gi
ve protection to the crofters you see, as Liberals, and so th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid684950\charrsid14301207 ey just put in this Captain Western went in uno}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
pposed every year and that was that and they didn't bother about politics. It's not like nowadays, they didn't just bother much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But the Liberals were the crofters party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were the crofters party. And - and that was that you see. Gladstone get them the crofters act you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was your mother the same really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, the same, yes, they did - they really didn't bother all that much about politics you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you remember your mother or father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Before 1919? Yes, well - well - I - I - yes, they weren't - there was no voting just here, they had to go to the island of Yell. The M
ail boat took them across there and took them back. And I remember them going to just once before 1919, to the island of Yell there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And he would have voted Liberal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Would vote Liberal, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 In some places at that time mend felt they r
isked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if your father felt under this kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, that - that must have been before because there was no interference at all of the old landlord 
about that - that - that was - that was - that was - that - that was not in my father's time, that was never mentioned you see. The reason of that may have been that Sir Arthur Nicholson, the first - the - the Sir Arthur Nicholson of that age was a man th
a
t never went out from his won castle much, you never heard much about it. He just confined himself to his own home and he didn't bother about - anything, as long as you pay your rent though, that he bothered about. Politics was a thing - it was very secon
dary importance in those days you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Your parents didn't take part in any political activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, no, no. No, no. No, no, no. No, no. Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - 
when they were not doing their work - well you see - in those days - the old - the men of the house did a lot of - they had lots of work they did in their spare time like things like making - you know this - the - the outfit for the ponies to carry, peat}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5577548\charrsid14301207 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207  
and things and all these straw baskets and what have you. That - that; took up the peoples time a lot, especially about the winter nights you know. So - and my mother would - would - would knit. So that there's always something to do you know. And - and I
'll tell you another - sometimes about the nights - some of the neighbours would come in about the night and have a chat and that sort of thing and that was - that was - so there was always something - I don't think that they complained of lon}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557947\charrsid14301207 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 liness you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Such as - what did you have in mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Nowadays they go to women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557947\charrsid14301207 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 s institutes or classes of some sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, well - well you see - no, well you see she couldn't get to the Women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11557947\charrsid14301207 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 s - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557947\charrsid14301207 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
uilds. The daughters could get but - she - she couldn't very well leave home, she - she didn't - she felt that she couldn't leave home to go to the Women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557947\charrsid14301207 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 s Guilds and things so she - she didn't go to that. It was - it did - it was more spinsters and single women that went to that things. Had more time you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh yes, oh yes, she would go out, oh yes. She would have gone maybe to the shop along some friends and - and sitting for a good while of the even
ing and - so on and so forth and they would be glad to see her and - and hadn't seen her for a while and all that sort of thing, oh yes, there - there was - there was that about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did she go out and visit other women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, yes, she'd maybe go to the shop, some fine day and - she'd take a walk about the shop, then she'd ca}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11557947\charrsid14301207 ll along friends, maybe a hour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207  there where the shop is and - some of the relations and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 She went by herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, went by herself, yes, yes, yes. Take a day off like. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well when he was working as a serving man to the Minister, is that what you'd mean? Well he - he would get home maybe - about seven or eight o'clock in summer and earl
ier with the dark nights in the winter you know. That's when he was - of course when he was a police - in the police force we didn't see him he was in Lerwick and Baltasound you see. We didn't see him much then. Except he could come over - over the weeken
d you know. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 If he wasn't away like this would he spend all he evenings at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well generally yes, except but - but - he would go up to a neighbour's house then. See that - that - was carried on a good deal. That - that neighbour would
 come down to - our house and have a yarn. And then he would go up to them then the other night and so on and - that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did they play cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well not - sometimes they wouldn't do anything, they would just have a chat you know, speak bout the fish
ing and - one thing and another. Draughts was a great - was a good game at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did people drink on these occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, no, no, they didn't drink, no, no, they didn't - they didn't. You mean strong drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 I meant beer or whisky?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, no, they - they - no, not - here again Feltar was rather took you a while to get that you see. There was nobody selled it you }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557947\charrsid14301207 see. The merchants wasn't licens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 ed to sell liq}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557947\charrsid14301207 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 or, you see, that's the thing. Except they had a bit of on the sly about them you know. Yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your father go to any clubs or any activities outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Not - no, no, not outside the island, no, no. Not outside the island.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were there any men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557947\charrsid14301207 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 s clubs on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - not - not at those
 days - no. The only thing was you see was - Young Mens - Bible Lecturing by the Ministers, both - both of them. The Free Church man would have his ones and the Church. That was carried on a good deal. Yes, yes. Religious teaching was very important in th
ose days you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 So there wasn't any sport your father took part in either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Sport? Well there would be occasional game of football, is that what you mean by sport? Aye, aye, the would gather together sometimes, the men would have a game of football you know. Very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your father and mother belong to anything lie a savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
You mean - no, no, they didn't do - you see the whole reason being you see that the people didn't have no money to spare to put into these things becau
se you see the people of Shetland in those days was poor. Because you see - the reason being that really speaking you see they couldn't make a lot of money to lift comfortably off the small croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Some people belonged to funeral clubs where they put a little by to pay for funerals and things like that didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, no, they didn't do that, no. What they did do you see when people was getting old and nearing the end of their time they would try to save up and put something by - into the hands o
f the - one of the family and see that they didn't have a pauper's funeral, you know. They'd have something to bury them. That - that was done very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh all right, I got on all right with them, all right, I - yes, yes, I - I - I've no difficulties that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was there any one of them that you felt particularly close to when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well I - I think I liked my sister - she was my age you know, she was - we were great friends
 because she was next to - near my age you see. We were always out together. I think there was that about it. And she - I think she had a liking for me too. Yes, yes, yes, so we - she - being the same age you know. Sometimes we'd go to seek gulls eggs in 
land. Well she'd be my age and we'd always go together you see, and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Who did you play with when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - well - well I had plenty of brothers. George - my brother George is the next one to me younger well we always played together.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you play with just your brother or your sister as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - and the other young fellows on the - on the township you know. Neighbours. We all played together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh well - all sorts of thing
s. In winter we had sledge. We would make a sledge and slid down these slopes you know. And all sorts of things. We would snare birds. You know. Make loops with horsehair on a stake you know and then put seed so that when the bird was walking around eatin
g they would put their foot in the snare, we thought that great fun. You know, snaring birds. You know, and all sorts, all sorts. All sorts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 So you could play anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Anywhere, no, there were no restrictions. And then I'll tell you what - when 
they took in the corn - they would build them into these - what do you call them - what would you call that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Stooks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - no, stooks when they're on the rigs. Set up a few sheaves together, that's stooks. But - but when they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
