r says, well I've seen that before, that man said. And she's hanging on a hair, ready to drop, you stay there. And - and the neighbours keep silent and - and - you know, we - we were taught don't make any noise until she gets back into the hole again and 
t
hey - she started, you know, the - to get the bright - to get back to - as the shadow was passing over. Well she got a back to the usual - now, they said, that's splendid, now all's well, go and make some tea. That shows you how they didn't know - how tha
t
 - that seems so very long ago now. 'Cos everybody knows now it's the shadow passing between you see, everybody knows what the eclipse is now. But that shows - that time back, they didn't know so very much you see. That was the want of radio and - and pap
ers and books and things to read you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well - well yes, we had that on the island. We had that. Because - this - this - there's a few people you know - the Ministers}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3031714\charrsid14301207  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 thought themselves a bit above us. But the landlords thought themselves a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3031714\charrsid14301207 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 ood lot above us. But there was a class in the island - you know the better off people the
n, that thought themselves a little bit superior to the lower fellow. They were - they maybe wouldn't show it too much but we could easy see it was there, that they thought themselves - is that what you're meaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 I was thinking of the landlords and the Ministers as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, oh yes, well they - they of course - we knew that they were superior to us of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How many landlords were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh there was two. There were two here. The Nicholsons and the Chains. That was living here.
 I'm not sure if I've got you right, are you meaning - you're meaning - that some people pretend or think that they were better, is that the way you mean? Well - well, yes, there were certain well to do people, the better class people like. Well - big - w
e considered them as a little bit super}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3031714\charrsid14301207 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 or because they were better off. Is that what you're meaning? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Which group would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh well - well - those days, being a big family - poorer class - we would have had to have said 
we were under privileged you see. But those who were perhaps shepher}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3031714\charrsid14301207 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
s to the landlord and - maybe left a bit of money, maybe some rich relation left them some money you see, if they were well to do, that would be the - better class of people. They could dress better and so on and so on, you see what I mean. If you get -;

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What position were the shopkeepers in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh they would have been in the better class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, and that would be the better class. And - and the flunkies. The flunkie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3031714\charrsid14301207 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
. That would be - that'll be the footmen and the general gardeners of that big houses there. Lee Garth or Brough Lodge. Sort of a footmen or men servant. They would be the better class.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 So there were the landlords, very much on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And then there's the ordinary people, but in between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And the ministers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But between the ministers and the ordinary people are these people like shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes. Yes, yes, I - I - we could - well - they - they being 
better off we had to set them as slightly superior person. Mind you they were not better really speaking, but they - they - they were better off and they knew that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another? Did you touch your}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3031714\charrsid14301207  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 cap or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh yes, yes, oh yes. For instance when we met the teacher we'd to lift our cap. And we met the Minister we - then we had to sort of - address him someway. Oh yes, we learned that at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was there anyone you called sir or master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well, yes, yes, we - yes, we'd the doctor was sir, the minister was sir, the laird Sir Arthur Nicholson was sir. They were the sirs. You called the Minister sir. The doctor was sir. And the teacher. The teacher was, if he was a male he was sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And female?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh ma'am, yes, ma'am, no ma'am, whatever it was,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did anyone show respect to your parents in this kind of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no. No, no, not to ordinary people, no, no, not toward ordinary people, no, no, no, no. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Would you come into any contact with the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, yes. You would work for the landlord, you would shear his sheep and - all that sort of thing you know and - cut his peats and all that at the rent time. Then he used to square up with you and that - pay you and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was this you personally or was it your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh well - well - latterly I had - m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3031714\charrsid14301207 y father that then, but lat}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 terly when it came to me I met the landlord a lot, yes, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was there any social distinction between the chapel and the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You mean ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 There were two denominations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh no, no, they each went to their own church you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were the kind of people who went to one, the United free and ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh yes, yes. No, well you see the United Free church went to their church. Then the established church went to theirs, but - if a Minister happened to be absent or sick or something, they should have gone at Sunday night to the oth
er church. You know what I mean? Su-posing say now that the Free church Minister was away at the General Assembly and the church closed, or - or sick - if he had the 'flu or that well - and if it was a fine night the other people said, well we'll go away 
to the Free church. And we'll say, oh well, we'll go away to the established church you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But in England there was quite a lot of social distinction between church and chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 The sort of upper middle classes going to church and the top people going to chapel, that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was there anything like this here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, not - not very much, only what - what was you know, there was a good deal of - of feeling towards your own church. The United Free Church w
as very staunch people the United Free and the other side was the same to their church. Each thought their denomination best. See what I mean? The United Free church thought their church - their denomination was best did the United Free church. The other 
established church, that people thought that was the best church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But there wasn't any social distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, no, but - the ones that think themselves higher that - the others though. They didn't think - they were maybe a little of that, the est
ablished church see that the landlord belonged to that one. I think that they thought themselves a little bit superior but it wasn't much. It was - it was more church loyalty that - that came into it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were some families thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, oh yes, oh yes, yes, yes. Oh you got that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You talk about the ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Yes, oh yes, yes, yes. Oh yes. Oh yes. You know some people's rough, oh yes, that class was a rough family. A very rough family. Very. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How many families would be counted as rough then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well you - you got that too, you got certain families - you know - by rough I take you mean always into trouble - is that - oh there were maybe half a dozen on the island that was always in some trouble or another. Fighting and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8346267\charrsid14301207 - scolding or having some - feu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
d about themselves, yes, oh yes. But the one I can remember most was that Clark family. Clark the name, at the west side of the island, they were always into trouble. Always. Always. The - the boy
s had a hole bored in the roof you know - just up you know, the ceiling and - and it - where the father would lie sleeping they would I they would - they were - they would have a small hole and they would drop down water on their father sleeping in the ch
a
ir. Well then there'd be a quarrel you see. You see what I mean? All that sort of thing. And they say that that boys - in the oven - put a young pig and roasted it - put him alive and then played out, I suppose when the mother come in the young pig had st
arted to smell - and the fat running out the stove then the pig was roasted alive, that - that was - that was - that was very bad you know. Yes, that was a bad family that. They were always into some sort of scrapes and trouble you know. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your father and mother have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well they had the to accept the fact that the richest people was their way of - they had to look up to them a bit. See what I mean? And where - where a man - maybe had a fiel
d of oxen and a new plough and a new cart - where the poorer people couldn't get that, then they - they had to really look at them as - as a bit superior. There was that about it. They would have though a man like that was - was - was superior to them. Th
e
y get - for the reason, they had no sale value. You maybe have got a neighbour - the ragged - the ragged sleeve keeps the hand back, ever heard that? You see, the ragged sleeve keeps the hand back. If people's poor they take a back seat. Regardless of wha
t their personal qualities are. Yes, well, yes, all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was it possible at that time to move - from one group to another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, I - you could move from one group to another if you got the means. If you - if you - if you fell into - if you s
truck luck and you had got a bit of go - good diggings or - or had a good two or three years at the waling, Greenland whaling and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5256326\charrsid14301207 the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 men came back with a good bit of money they - you moved up to the better class you see. Well if you hadn't much money you had to keep down just where you were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What about getting to be a teacher or a Minister, by getting some education and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, well you see - that wasn't done so much in those days, they - they were imported. See - yes, that - but the peop
le - the main lot of the Merchant Navy or the Merchant Service that got to be up - ticket men like skippers or mates and - officers, second officer and - that - that was - that put them up see a bit. But there wasn't so many teachers, if you need - if the
y needed a teacher they just said, we're getting one from Glasgow or here or there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 If one of the boys did well at school could they go on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, oh yes, oh yes, yes, yes, yes, yes. If they had the brains they could go get on. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, I - I can remember - that. Many - many - many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Who was this then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well - do you mean at the - what class do you mean in? Well Mistress Campbell was a ver
y fine woman, the Minister's wife. And - and - and I always said that Lady Nicholson - the one before - well she - she's going a couple of generations back, she was a very kind woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What was there about her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well I'll tell you what you see, al
though she was a very - although she was a Lady and a woman of independent means she would always lend a handing help to the poor. And I - there - there were a woman that was in debt to Sir Arthur, her husband, and she - came with - Lady Nicholson had gre
at buying of fine lace, shawls and hosiery, and this girl - and this woman was a great knitter. And - she came to Sir Arthur, she came to Lady Nicholson with two big shawls. Lady Nicholson wanted them to send to friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you remember seeing a policeman around here when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - oh yes, oh yes, yes, yes. The policeman came in when there were any - any - any - any law}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5256326\charrsid14301207 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 bre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5256326\charrsid14301207 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
kers or anything you know. The first policeman we saw was - was when a - there was a man, he was not just exactl
y right and was sort of mental you see and he wouldn't pay his rent. And - the - of course he was sued and the police came, took him away you see. We thought this strange - he was a - they wouldn't run no risk with him, he was sort of a - they wouldn't - 
so they had hand - cuffs on him and we thought - there were two of them, we thought this was great sight, children - going past with -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did they have to come specially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, oh no, they had to come special. In such cases like that when th
ere were any special circumstances they'd be - have to come you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did you think of the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - oh well me father was a police so we were sort of - used to it you know. We thought - well we just knew that he was just doing a job yo
u see. We - we rather stood - well we thought - we looked up to him as a - well we would be afraid to be sort of afraid of them then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How do you think the police treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - as some thought they shouldn't have handcuffed that man. Some of the local people. But I - they maybe had to do it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh yes, oh we all paid rents to - to the landlord, yes, yes, yes. According to the crofts you had. One croft would be a little over four pounds you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Four pounds for how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh for - for the croft and the house. A year, yes. That'd be one croft, six acres of arable you see. And then a hill - a right to the hill. The whole thing would be about four pound ten but generally about the average of tha
t. Of course you had two pound and you paid eight pound if had two crofts you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did you feel about the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - our landlord was rather bad landlord, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well I could - could I put in a little story
? Well - well when the same man that I am telling you about belonged to the other landlord - they changed -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 The one who was handcuffed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes. The Chains estate then, perhaps you've heard about them. That's the big house you see down at Lee Garth
 there, that - that estate. Well when they were going down past the house at Brough Lodge, that's another - our landlord. Then he - with the old - with the man handcuffed like this, with the police at each side. And Sir Arthur Nicholson they took a son, a
n
 heir - a son and heir, the young chap who would become other successor. He says, do you see that? Pointed out the - the dining - the sitting room window. He said, I do father. Well, he said, that could never happen with me. See that it doesn't happen wit
h
 you. Meaning you see that - that the man was just not right exactly. And they shouldn't nave done that to a man that wasn't - all right. Well that - that was the - and another way, he would offer to help people to - to improve their houses if they didn't
 have the means themselves, so we had no complaints of our landlord. That would be true to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But the other landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well he - he - he - the other landlord was not such a humane man then you may say. He was - not nearly so much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh we - we all knew that. We all knew that on - on the small crofts you know. We - as we mentioned the last time - last night on the other recording - these small crofts was all r
ight - it was a good enough quiet home but hardly enough - income to keep large families so it was a struggle. Even some of the well to do people had a bit of a struggle you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What difference did it make to your family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well it meant a good lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How did it affect you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well the effect was that we would have had much harder times. We had to make do with much less food for instance. And maybe eat more potatoes and fish. We couldn't get the luxuries and things from the shops you see. That made a big difference. You see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How often was your father ill, do you remember him being ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - he - well he - he - well no, he - not so much. Not so very much, you see my father - when he worked 
for that Minister the Minister maybe wouldn't bother give him to a lot of work but he would buy meal, send for meal and that sort of thing. He would say, well I - you'll be requiring a flour meal for the family. My father say, yes. Well he would just send
 off for meal and things, he wanted a lot for the poorer people the Minister. That was then all right you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 The minister helped poor people generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, oh he was very good the Minister, very good indeed. Very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Where did he get his money from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well you see - he was - he was - he was - he was a single man. Well he had to pay a housekeeper and then he fell into a little money, his father was a rich farmer. In Scotland you see, so he fell in - he was the only son, he had some 
money after his father. So he - he - he had a little money you see. And other thing he would do you see - he knew that the poor people couldn't pay these central funds and - and funds for the United Free church you see it was - it was - they needed more f
u
nds than the other church that got from the state but that was a free church kept up by the people. So instead of going around with - asking them for that money he would send up money to the church of Edinburgh himself. And that was very good of him. He k
new that the poor people didn't have anything to give which he sent up money himself, he said, well that's from the congregation. And that's the sort of man he was. Very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were there any Guardians or people gave out other help or money or anything lik- that any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well well, yes, yes, that's a very good question because you see - in the - there were sort of a Parish Council then, you see, and there were what was called a poor box, you maybe never heard that, a box that there was m
oney put from the church, spare money then. It was mostly the established church that had the spare money, they put it - in what they called the poor box. You'll not be heard maybe about that before? Well, well then. But - it's the last people would have 
l
iked to have done was to have accept money out of the poor box. They wouldn't have liked to have done it then. And - among the fellows that would have given them place that was just about the last of them. So they didn't really like to take that. They wou
ld rather - gone hungry and not take out the poor box then. I remember that - quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 If people were hard up for some reason, perhaps because the man was ill, who would help, the Minister then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no. No - but all the - I'm afraid that there
 was not very many. If you had a good merchant, come here and tell - he would say, well - you're in a difficulty, I'll not refuse you meal for your children. You may get it paid up sometime. That - that - that's what happened. That would be done.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were there any charities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No. There were really no charities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No kind of relief or workhouse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No. The only relief there was as I tell you had to get something out of the poor box. That's all it was. Or - and - or - or then you could have gone
 on the board. Aye. That is to say - supposing say now a spinster or somebody which had had no provided at all, then they would go on the board. That meant to say they would have to get them money to keep them going. There were a few like that here you kn
ow. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Who was the board?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well, it - it - it was the parish council would put through application to the authorities at Lerwick. For the - for the country council and that sort of thing and they would allocate so much money to poor destitute pe
ople. You see. And ten there was another thing. There - there were some societies would send up charity clothing around here. We didn't see much of that. That was getting the favours you know. That - that - that went on on a small scale. Charity clothing 
you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you ever get any help from any of these sources?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, we never got no help. Yes you see, my father for the most of his time worked at that Minister. And - and - and that provided food - meal - that sort of - then he was a policeman for a time.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5256326\charrsid14301207  So - we - we - there were more}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207  families off as we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did he have to do for the Minister exactly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well you see the Minister had a croft. Just as we have. And he - he did - he had to do the Minister worked this croft, had to put
 out manure and - help with the ploughing and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 So it was crafting work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
So it was crafting work. And - and then - well - well - he worked about the Manse too, the Minister would set a lot of cabbage and vegetables and dig that up and - all sort
s of things. He always had something to do. And then the Minister had a part - you see that part that's around this part up on there - well the minister had all that for hay. The minister had a cow or two, so he had to cut all that with a scythe, cure it 
and see - so the minister - there was always some work to do there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
If someone did something that people disapproved of how did they show their disapproval, was there any way in which they showed their disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - would you be meaning - children or grown ups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 In England people talk about people making rough music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You know that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 I know. Well - if - if - if a - if it was children or scholars then the school board would deal with that, but - if it was grown ups
 you see - well if it - they would have to do something fairly bad, the only way they could deal with them was to - was - report it to the police or the procurator fiscal of Lerwick. But t-hat would have to be doing something }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5256326\charrsid14301207 v}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 ery bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Not breaking the law but if people did something that was not approved of by the other people, but was not illegal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes. I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did they make rough music or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - they had to take a lot of that. And say very little. I'll tell you in
 the very old days - going back a bit - you'll not have heard this but - but I can explain that to you - there was a good deal of corn stealing went on. If you had a lot of corn and I was short you see - well I would go in your yard, take a rope and maybe
 
tie about a dozen or so sheaves on a dark night. Well if you met me - and you thought you were as a good a man as I was or better then you would - accuse me right away and you - you maybe - you with your fists on me. Well I - I - if I got the worst of it 
I'd take that. There's not much to do about it, I had to be - take my medicine like a man if you - set about me. But it had to be pretty bad offence. be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5256326\charrsid14301207 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 ore it was fought over. Oh there were always Justice of Peace's, aye, that's what you would do now, I fo
rgot, I nearly forgot. There was always Justice of Peace in the island. There's two now. There's Andrew Cook and Charles Brown. And - and - and they would report - they would report to the Justice of the Peace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But if people didn't like somebody how did they show it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were there any ways of making people ashamed of themselves or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well - do you mean actually doing an off}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 nce, is that what you mean? Or do you mean if they didn't like a chap? Well I'll tell
 you - then - if they didn't like a chap they would say well - they would have as little to do with him as possible. Give him the cold shoulder thing. Just say, well that's not a good fellow, what - we'll just steer clear of that chap. They wouldn't hurt 
them or anything like that, they just let them go their own way. Keep at a distance you know, that's what they'd do with a chap like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were you given any lessons by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no. No lessons by your parents, no, no. The only time you might }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 
have asked, but that's at your S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
unday school, if your parents and mother was a good scholar and you were doing some skit of some Sunday school lessons, she - you would consider be more best out of the Bible - better than the Bible you were, you were 
asked something about that. But - you - you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14301207  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 you didn't ask your parents about that really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well we - we were - we went at our ages to school, I told you all about it, we went six years of age in our age going in my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What time in the morning did school begin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - oh - no, no, I think then you had to arrive at nine o'clock - Nine o'clock the; school opened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh we come - was it - four o'clock when we come back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh - well - just a public school - a - it was a building built for the purpose, quite a good building you know. For olden days - a small building but - the - it was a quite a good - could hold about between
 fifty and sixty children, there were the desks and blackboards and - quite good building you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 It took all the children on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, yes, indeed yes. Yes. When I was - I think that there was about fifty-eight children all of them you
ng when I was - and two teachers. Two teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How did you get to school and how long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh now - we had to travel on foot. We either went over the hill - or - followed the road. The road was longer. The hill was the shorter.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - it would have taken us about an hour. Well - well say - say - maybe three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 quarters of an hour take. That was fair good time, three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 quarters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 And you went by yourself did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, we all - we went in a
 crowd, just - we would wait for that children coming over from the east each side and join up with them and - off we would go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you have your midday meal at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well, no, no, you would take bread and an orange with you. Then when 
that Highland teacher, Miss Mcleaod came she said I am going to see if I can improve things. So she had a - a - entertainment and so trained us up to sing and recite and so on. A concert. Well - well then she invited the people of the island to this and h
ad the tickets sixpence each. And that went towards some cocoa. That went on for years. Other teachers after that took it up. That -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You brought some food with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, then had the cocoa - at midday. Yes, I - yes, I - that's the how the food - eating system was carried on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did you get given for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh well - what I did take from home. Oh you just take a piece of bacon bread like what you see there on that dresser. Something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 A bit of bacon and a bit of bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, no, just a piece of that bread maybe with a little butter between it. Just a piece like that that you see there. Well that's the kind we would take, maybe one-one piece of that. Maybe we would take two pieces but we could only afford one piece.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well you see, I - I think that when you're young you really never like school. The most. I don't think we really liked school. Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Why not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well why did the reasons was - we - we got one Fetlar ma
n, Brown the name was for a teacher, we thought it very hard on us, he had a piece of - what you call a Strop don't you? Yes, a trawse or a strap made of the - if we were bad he would strike away at our hands and we didn't like it. We felt as if we'd been
 stung - a big - with a - with a - with - we'd have struck back. We }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 didn't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 - I don't think we really liked school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Because you didn't like the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 We didn't like the teacher and we just didn't - the whole thing, we didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were the lessons dull then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - the lessons would be dull. And maybe get wet clothes - wet going to school. Maybe our feet would be cold but - all we had on was boots. Which didn't make you like it. And I'll tell you another reason why we really did no
t like the school was for that home lessons. We hated this. Home lessons you know. Well - well - well - homework, well no you see, take - Wolsley's farewell to Dreyfus, you know that Well - well, say - say - one of the poems you know - say - you know abou
t some of them, say Robert the Bruce - Bruce and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 spicier}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
, something like that, or the Inchcape Rock, you know Robert the Bruce? Well - well - King Bruce of Scotland laid a - throw himself down on a lonely moor to think and true he was a man more like a 
down, but his heart was beginning to sink, for he had been trying to do great deeds to make his people glad. He tried and tried but couldn't succeed and so he became quite sad. Now what we had to do you see, we had to write the whole of that in our own wo
r
ds. And explain why King Bruce of Scotland did throw himself down and what it was all about. Maybe a couple of pages - we just hated that. And if we didn't do it then they'll keep us in. That sort - oh no, we didn't like the school, quite frankly, we didn
't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did the teachers emphasi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 e certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Like what sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - Miss McLeod emphasised that you were no use except you were well mannered. Now you had to be that. And - anothe
r man emphasised that you were no good unless you were good at arithmetic - if - if you couldn't do that then you're just no use at any job. And so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What about tidiness and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, all that, yes, all that - counted very much. They tried to - all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What about ways of speaking?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, they would - they didn't - they werena so particular about that. The - the fact of the matter is they didn't really try to learn us to speak proper English the way you speak 
it. They should have done that. You know, because you see this children had to go out in the world to earn a living. And there was no use learn them Shetland or Scotch, it was no use. You see what I mean? We - wem - they should have started off to learn t
o speak English and to speak a sound English, sound the word the way you do it. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 With punishment did they treat the girls the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - no, they - they - well - I'm afraid - no - no, no the girls got off for - much ligh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 er than
 we did. But not very often. Rare when Arthur Brown when he was teaching he punished the girls. He did punish one or two but - I'm afraid that - of course the boys were more mischievous you see. But I - I - I would say that the girls went - got off much l
ighter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
here any other punishments apart from this t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 awse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Yes, they would be - he - he would say - say - sent you in the corner. He would put you in a corner. See? One of - one of the greatest punishments we was keeping you in - after - ke
ep when the others was gone. What was that? Oh yes, well - well then - then - then - we'd the slte, we had the slates in those days. Well then the teacher would say, all right, write at the top - let me see - yes, well - I should not use insolence to othe
r people. Or I shouldn't push girls around in a bad mannered fashion, then you'd to write that five or six hundred times, that was it. The worst was - the worst was keeping you in. That was a bad punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What kind of things were you punished of then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh - all sorts of things. All sorts of things. I don't know - oh - well, fighting was one another, if she seen a mark on your face she would know that you had been fighting. Well that was an offence. And bullying the younger children, that was an 
offence. And knocking them over. And - and - and sometimes do that again they'll call leading you 'til the blind binds nurse, that was closing your eyes and making you walk with this, maybe circling you round so you couldna see and shifting you and put yo
ur nose down on about cows droppings see, like that, that was bad. Yes, yes. Anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - up to a point.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well they would ask you but - their interest in scholarship at those days would \{ILLEGIBLE\} No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did they visit the school or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - some of the - I tell you, some of them might have gone to the teacher. If his - if - if the teacher - if there wer
e any - offence like, if the - if the - if this child was being accused of anything you see. Then their parent would go and make an inquiry into this to wee that - see what was wrong and maybe if he thought the teacher was doing - bullying then he would -
 he would - he would threaten to report them to the authorities, that were done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well - we always thought that the teachers had favourites. We always had th
at impression. And they got the better chance. That would be the children of maybe say the - the clerk of the school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
board or anything like that. We always thought that they had favourites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How did they treat them differently then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well, 
the - well they would be let off - for the same thing that another one would have got punished. Did you think that, that teachers had favourites? We always thought at these - these places here. We always had that feeling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - oh yes, yes, yes, oh the west side of the island, the boys - and the east side, there - there was a line like the burn there. That side was the west side and this was the east side and there would always be some rough play and
 fighting between the two, that went on for many many years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 That was the main division among the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, I - yes, the boys - not the girls - but the boys, a lot of horseplay and fighting between the - the two sides.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Were there any children who were left out of things at school? Some who didn't join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well I'll tell you, there were always the backward child was kept out of things. A - a backward child you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But there' weren't any who were socially superior or socially inferior or that kind of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well not in our time but - in the olden days with the Minister's sons - was - was at the school, they were counted a bit superior.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 That was before your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Before my time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well we - we - we - the leaving age at my time was fourteen. Fourteen years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Would you have stayed longer if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, I don't think any of us really would. I don't think so. Because you see,
 we saw no future for us except going to sea. The Merchant Service. That's all the future the boys saw. In }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207  days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh aye, we went sometimes to a night school, yes, a night school, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What was that in connection with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh that was a higher grade of - of - you may say a higher grade of arithmetic and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What made you go to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - we really - it was the fashion of those days for a few of the people to go and the
 one would say to the other, well - do you think we'll go to night school for a few months? We'd say, yes, well we'll try it. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You did this yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, and all the other chaps around about, we'd all go. But we didn't like you see, what w
e didn't like if any of these teachers came away with - with - with the difficult - too difficult - standard of - of education for us, we wouldn't like that, we'd stay at home then. And we thought it beyond us then - to cope with the thing. Then we just l
eft off going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well - no, I - I can't say that I do because I believe you know if the truth was said - if we - not me but generally I believe that the old pupils that I was with - some dead and
 some are alive and we would keep - hold our own with some of the youngsters now. You know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, we - yes, we benefited, yes. Yes yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 While you were at school did you have a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Or any means or earning a little money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, no, there was no earning of money here. Not at the school age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - what was my first full time job? Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well I believe it'd be true to say that when I joined the war at seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What did you do between fourteen and seventeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well - well you see what we did then we just did odd jobs then. Odd jobs, we - we helped people with peats, we'
d maybe do a little work for the landlord along with the men. And - various bits of jobs - like say these - when my brother got a job you know, Tommy, he got a job to the West Ministers, serving men then. Well they - when there was anything on like the sh
e
aring sheep or - driving up sheep - - that Minister had a farm you know - or any things like that then he would sand word to me - or peats to come over - and give a hand you see. Well - the Minister's wife would pay you, and do odd sort of jobs like that.
 Then cutting peats was a great business. And - and - and cutting corn with a scythe you know, scythe. And - and just odd jobs around where - the - the place you see, the people and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Any money you earned like that, did you give it to your mother or did you keep it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - first of all you would get yourself a pair of boots. And then - for the winter, and then you would give it to your people. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 So your first full time jobs was in the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh in the Navy, in my case, yes, full time job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 That's when you were seventeen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes. That's right, at seventeen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How did you get it, did you just volunteer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, oh but the war broke out you see. And they - they - they said - they asked for volunteers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Where did you have to go to volunteer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh we had to go to Lerwick, join up at boatyard at Lerwick, of course we telled the - we all told a white lie about our age, you see}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16545636\charrsid14301207 , we had to be eighteen to enro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 l. We said we were eighteen. They didn't ask
 to see your birth certificate. They would have known we were telling lies. Well I was big for my age and we all - us chaps that joined up we were sort of big for our ages. They didn't ask - say nothing about it, just enrolled us. Medical examinations the
n on with the un}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11473416\charrsid14301207 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 form and start training you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How much were you paid in the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - what - what - I remember what we were paid. We got twenty-three shillings per week mind you. But out of that we had to pay ten shillings for our digs, we lived in a boarding house. That was what - what - we'd thirteen shillings over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh in Lerwick - at the boarding house. Oh Lerwick in the town of Lerwick you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 This was when you were training?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, that's when we were training. That's before we went out foreign service you know. Before we went to the wars fighting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How long did you stay in the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well I - I stayed 'til the finish of hostilities. 'Til the war was over. You know. Finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 What jobs have you done since the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - well - along with the croft, we've been at various - well we - I - I was at the soapstone - the mining of soapstone, the talk you know, the soapstone for a while few years. Oh the Scottish Mineral Company,
 was at Fetlar, the east side you know. And then they - they - they had a disagreement with the landlord about - with the Chains about the land. They thought they werena paying them enough for royalties you see in money and so they - they - they - there w
as a disagreement and they-this place was closed down, that was the end of that lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 How long did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 For a number of years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Was that a full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, that was full time, summer and winter. Yes, yes. Well here now 
we're the jack of all trades you know. Oh making rods and mending boots, I - I - I was a - did a lot of boot mending and making and mending, that sort of thing. Harnesses - harnesses and horse collars and things, sort of a jack of all trades and the maste
r of none. Then when me father died you see then this croft fell to my you see. My older brother settled in Liverpool and he didn't want to transfer the thing over to me and I just stopped here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Apart from the Navy and working on the soapstone you haven't had any full time employment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Not, no full time - not full time - of course I - I - like all sorts of things like that you know, sort of - you know sidelines then. You see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Your registrar now, how long}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16545636\charrsid14301207  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 have you been registrar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
I - and - and - oh I've been a long time registrar. Number of years. I was assistant - assistant first and then the man - he - he retired and it fell to me. I've been a long time now. Number of years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Would you have preferred another type of job from being a crofter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Well - not now. See because - taking your retirement pension and that you wouldn't bother - I think though really if I had to live my life over again I would have been like all the boys, I think I would have gone to sea. I would 
have did, yes, I - I would have gone to sea. It's a sort of - all the Laurenson's my people were seamen, my grandfathers were all that you see, I'd have gone to sea, I wouldn't have taken up land at all. I - I have a regret there that I didn't. But it was
 me mother left a widow, I stopped on to help her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Someone had to take on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Someone had to take - but I - I always felt sorry I didn't follow a seafaring life. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 So you didn't belong to a trades union or professional organisation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 No, no, no, no, no, no. Oh no. There was no union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You were living at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You lived at home for three years after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Then you went in the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When you came back from the war you went on living with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Exactly, yes, yes, exactly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did leaving school change your}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16545636\charrsid14301207  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 way of life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did this make any difference to your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh no, no, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16545636\charrsid14301207 no, no, no-no. The parents knew}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207  we did that we left at fourteen and - and - and they didn't bother much about it. Me father would say, well boy, what are you going to do? You'll have to be looking out for your future. I'd 
say, oh well I'd like to go to sea. After a year or two. That's settled then. And the girls - my sisters, they'll - I'll like to go for settle for domestic service. Or something of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You weren't treated any different at home because you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
No, no, no, you see they knew that you left at fourteen years of age and that was that You see. They would be very glad of you for help with peats and things, they didn't - question anything like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you spend your Sundays any differently, did you go on going to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh but you see at those days you had to go to church, it was a most - because you - and if you didn't go to church with your parents your father and that - there was always at church in those days, then yo
u should go to make a difference - ill feeling so you had to go to church whether you liked it or not. And listen to that old Ministers dry sermon was maybe a pest but you had to do it, there was no other option, you had to do it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 When did you stop going to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh - well - we stopped going - when did we - maybe - when - well when you left the school then you knock off the Sunday school then. Yes, something like that, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 
Oh - oh when Shetlanders grow - when gets a bit - do you mean - what age is that do you mean - referring to - what age now? If you - what age do you mean then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Up 'til 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 I see. Well - the Shetlanders - those - naturally you see they have 
no other - time here to take off they - they do more or less keep in touch with politics from very young you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 But did you take any special interest yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well Yes, I - I did, yes, quite honestly I did. Of course we had a Liberal in Parl
iament and that was supposed to be the - the thing in those days you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you vote in the 1919 election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well you see - if - did I vote - twenty-one years of age, I would have started to vote then when the war - was about twenty-one. I
 - I - yes, well I expect I would, it was going to Yell to vote. Between Sir Malcolm Smith and Robert Hamilton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Who did you vote for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh - oh I - oh I will say the truth you know and I didn't vote for - for the Conservative man. I - I really did
. Sir Malcolm Smith, you see he was a very rich man. And he - he had done so much - he had given so much to the poor of the Shetland Islands, he gave gifts to buy coal and all things of that and we thought it - that was be - fair to vote for him so we vot
ed for him, but Hamilton got in. A Liberal you see. Now you needn't be frightened to ask, you could look around for your - go out asking -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 You told me earlier something of how you spent your spare time, your leisure activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did these change at all when you left school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Well no, not much. It didn't change very much. Not so very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you make any new friends when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 On the island? Well no not much really. 'Cos you see you didn't meet very many more 
friends after - after the school as when you had at school, no, you really didn't on a small island, no. You see, you were restricted there regarding friends. You - you may start to go after the girls. Got a bit older you would have done that. That sort o
f thing. Just a lot of boys together you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3488920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Did you have any special friends at this time, either boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9124922 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14894142\charrsid14301207 Oh yes, oh yes, we always had our boy - boy - our schoolboy sweetheart, oh yes indeed. We would have - the most of them. After scho
