. That - that's the toast they would give. Then of course after the - at the first feed then they would have to - the place was cleared for - for - for - for - for dancing. And the fiddler was sat up on the mill in the barn, on the hand mill. There they w
o
uld dance away - and dance away then, at - at - at maybe two or three o'clock - and - and - am I going too far? At three o'clock they're taking the bride to bed, that - tha's before my time. Then - they - they would put the - undress the bride and put her
 
to bed, the - women, and she would - and - and - and - and they throw their bouquet, but in this case the bride took off her stocking, close her eyes and throw like that and - and whoever the stocking fell on would be - would - the next bride. That was su
pposed to be lucky.
